column1: The prevalence of child marriage is defined as follows, and is presented in the columns expressed as a percentage (%):

column2: Percentage of women aged 20 to 24 years who were first married or in union before ages 15 and 18.
Percentage of men aged 20 to 24 years who were first married or in union before age 18.

column1: The burden of child marriage is defined as follows, and is presented in the columns expressed as an absolute number (n):

column2: Number of girls and women of all ages who were first married or in union before ages 15 and 18.
Values expressed as absolute numbers (n) have been rounded.
National data refer to the latest available data source per country.
Confidence intervals are not shown in this table. Caution is warranted in interpreting the results, as apparent differences across groups may not be statistically significant.

Regional and global figures are population-weighted averages of the latest available data per country, within a range of recent years. Regional aggregates represent data covering at least 50 per cent of the regional population.
Regions without sufficient population coverage are not shown in the summary section beneath the table.
Demographic data are from the United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division, World Population Prospects.
More information on the data can be found in the Technical Notes of the Child Marriage Data Portal, available here: https://childmarriagedata.org/about/
UNICEF global databases, based on Demographic and Health Surveys, Multiple Indicator Cluster Surveys, and other national surveys.
Prepared by the Data and Analytics Section; Division of Data, Analytics, Planning and Monitoring, UNICEF
